dlinkSwIfCounterMIB.name: dlinkSwIfCounterMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file.

dlinkSwIfCounterMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwIfCounterMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for displaying counters.

dIfCounterIfLinkChangeTable.name: dIfCounterIfLinkChangeTable
dIfCounterIfLinkChangeTable.description: This table is used to display the number of interface link change events.

dIfCounterIfLinkChangeEntry.name: dIfCounterIfLinkChangeEntry
dIfCounterIfLinkChangeEntry.description: Entry containing the number of interface link change events for a particular interface.

dIfCounterIfLinkChange.name: dIfCounterIfLinkChange
dIfCounterIfLinkChange.description: The number of interface link change events.

dIfCounterIfUtilizationTable.name: dIfCounterIfUtilizationTable
dIfCounterIfUtilizationTable.description: This table is used to display the utilization of ports.

dIfCounterIfUtilizationEntry.name: dIfCounterIfUtilizationEntry
dIfCounterIfUtilizationEntry.description: Entry contains the utilization information of a port.

dIfCounterIfUtilizationRx.name: dIfCounterIfUtilizationRx
dIfCounterIfUtilizationRx.description: This object indicates the current rate of received frames on the interface.

dIfCounterIfUtilizationTx.name: dIfCounterIfUtilizationTx
dIfCounterIfUtilizationTx.description: This object indicates the current rate of transmitted frames on the interface.

dIfCounterIfUtilizationUtil.name: dIfCounterIfUtilizationUtil
dIfCounterIfUtilizationUtil.description: This object indicates the percentage of the utilization on the interface.

dIfCounterClearAll.name: dIfCounterClearAll
dIfCounterClearAll.description: This object clears all counters, when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dIfCounterClearIf.name: dIfCounterClearIf
dIfCounterClearIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the physical port interface on which the counters will be cleared. When read, a value of 0 is returned.

dIfRxStatsTable.name: dIfRxStatsTable
dIfRxStatsTable.description: This table is used to display the receiving statistics not covered in standard MIBs (IF-MIB, RMON, BRIDGE-MIB, Etherlike-MIB) or extend the standard defined objects to 64 bits.

dIfRxStatsEntry.name: dIfRxStatsEntry
dIfRxStatsEntry.description: An entry contains receiving statistics on an interface.

dIfRxStatsHCPkts.name: dIfRxStatsHCPkts
dIfRxStatsHCPkts.description: The number of packets received on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of etherStatsPkts. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

dIfRxStatsHCPkts64Octets.name: dIfRxStatsHCPkts64Octets
dIfRxStatsHCPkts64Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This object is a 64-bit version of etherStatsPkts64Octets. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

dIfRxStatsHCPkts65to127Octets.name: dIfRxStatsHCPkts65to127Octets
dIfRxStatsHCPkts65to127Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). This object is a 64-bit version of etherStatsPkts65to127Octets. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

dIfCounterRxDropTable.name: dIfCounterRxDropTable
dIfCounterRxDropTable.description: This table consists of a list of receiving statistics for discarded packets on interfaces.

dIfCounterRxDropEntry.name: dIfCounterRxDropEntry
dIfCounterRxDropEntry.description: An entry contains the receiving statistics for discarded packets on an interface.

dIfCounterRxBufferFullDrops.name: dIfCounterRxBufferFullDrops
dIfCounterRxBufferFullDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded while input buffer full.

dIfCounterRxACLDrops.name: dIfCounterRxACLDrops
dIfCounterRxACLDrops.description: The total number of received packets denied by ACLs.

dIfCounterRxMulticastDrops.name: dIfCounterRxMulticastDrops
dIfCounterRxMulticastDrops.description: The total number of received multicast packet that is discarded.

dIfCounterRxVLANIngressDrops.name: dIfCounterRxVLANIngressDrops
dIfCounterRxVLANIngressDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by VLAN ingress checking.

dIfCounterRxIPv6Drops.name: dIfCounterRxIPv6Drops
dIfCounterRxIPv6Drops.description: The total number of IPv6 packets dropped by routing process.

dIfCounterRxSTPDrops.name: dIfCounterRxSTPDrops
dIfCounterRxSTPDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded when ingress port is not in forwarding state.

dIfCounterRxStormAndTableDiscard.name: dIfCounterRxStormAndTableDiscard
dIfCounterRxStormAndTableDiscard.description: The total number of packets discarded by receiving policy (e.g. the source or destination MAC is not allowed, rate limit, etc.)

dIfCounterRxMTUDrops.name: dIfCounterRxMTUDrops
dIfCounterRxMTUDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by frames received, which exceeds Maximum Frame in length and contains a valid or invalid FCS.

dIfCounterRxInvalidDestPort.name: dIfCounterRxInvalidDestPort
dIfCounterRxInvalidDestPort.description: The total number of packets dropped due to no destination port can be forwarded to.

dIfCounterRxBandwidthCtrlDrops.name: dIfCounterRxBandwidthCtrlDrops
dIfCounterRxBandwidthCtrlDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by port ingress bandwidth control.

dIfTxStatsTable.name: dIfTxStatsTable
dIfTxStatsTable.description: This table is used to display the transmitting statistics information not covered in standard MIBs (IF-MIB, RMON, BRIDGE-MIB, Etherlike-MIB) or extend the standard defined objects to 64 bits.

dIfTxStatsEntry.name: dIfTxStatsEntry
dIfTxStatsEntry.description: An entry contains transmitting statistics on an interface.

dIfTxStatsHCPkts.name: dIfTxStatsHCPkts
dIfTxStatsHCPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted on the interface. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of ifCounterDiscontinuityTime.

dIfTxStatsFCSErrors.name: dIfTxStatsFCSErrors

dIfCounterTxDropTable.name: dIfCounterTxDropTable

dIfCounterTxSTPDrops.name: dIfCounterTxSTPDrops
